HELP
----

- the -h option displays this help information on screen

List of parameters for the JPEG 2000 encoder:

REMARKS:
---------

The markers written to the main_header are : SOC SIZ COD QCD COM.
COD and QCD never appear in the tile_header.

- This coder can encode a mega image, a test was made on a 24000x24000 pixels 
color image.  You need enough disk space memory (twice the original) to encode 
the image,i.e. for a 1.5 GB image you need a minimum of 3GB of disk memory)

By default:
------------

 * Lossless
 * 1 tile
 * Size of precinct : 2^15 x 2^15 (means 1 precinct)
 * Size of code-block : 64 x 64
 * Number of resolutions: 6
 * No SOP marker in the codestream
 * No EPH marker in the codestream
 * No sub-sampling in x or y direction
 * No mode switch activated
 * Progression order: LRCP
 * No index file
 * No ROI upshifted
 * No offset of the origin of the image
 * No offset of the origin of the tiles
 * Reversible DWT 5-3

Parameters:
------------

Required Parameters (except with -h):
One of the two options -ImgDir or -i must be used

-ImgDir      : Image file Directory path (example ../Images) 
    When using this option -OutFor must be used

-OutFor 
    REQUIRED only if -ImgDir is used
	  Need to specify only format without filename <BMP>  
    Currently accepts PGM, PPM, PNM, PGX, BMP format

-i           : source file  (-i source.pnm also *.pgm, *.ppm) 
    When using this option -o must be used

-o           : destination file (-o dest.j2k or .jp2) 

Optional Parameters:

-h           : display the help information 
 
-cinema2k    : Digital Cinema 2K profile compliant codestream for 2K resolution.(-cinema2k 24 or 48) 
	  Need to specify the frames per second for a 2K resolution. Only 24 or 48 fps is allowed

-cinema4k    : Digital Cinema 4K profile compliant codestream for 4K resolution 
	  Frames per second not required. Default value is 24fps

-r           : different compression ratios for successive layers (-r 20,10,5)
 	         - The rate specified for each quality level is the desired 
	           compression factor.
		   Example: -r 20,10,1 means quality 1: compress 20x, 
		     quality 2: compress 10x and quality 3: compress lossless

               (options -r and -q cannot be used together)
 
-q           : different psnr for successive layers (-q 30,40,50) 
                (options -r and -q cannot be used together)
 
-n           : number of resolutions (-n 3) 

-b           : size of code block (-b 32,32) 

-c           : size of precinct (-c 128,128) 

-t           : size of tile (-t 512,512) 

-p           : progression order (-p LRCP) [LRCP, RLCP, RPCL, PCRL, CPRL] 

-s           : subsampling factor (-s 2,2) [-s X,Y] 
	     Remark: subsampling bigger than 2 can produce error

-POC         : Progression order change (-POC T1=0,0,1,5,3,CPRL/T1=5,0,1,6,3,CPRL) 
      Example: T1=0,0,1,5,3,CPRL 
			 : Ttilenumber=Resolution num start,Component num start,Layer num end,Resolution num end,Component num end,Progression order

-SOP         : write SOP marker before each packet 

-EPH         : write EPH marker after each header packet 

-M           : mode switch (-M 3) [1=BYPASS(LAZY) 2=RESET 4=RESTART(TERMALL)
                 8=VSC 16=ERTERM(SEGTERM) 32=SEGMARK(SEGSYM)] 
                 Indicate multiple modes by adding their values. 
                 ex: RESTART(4) + RESET(2) + SEGMARK(32) = -M 38

-x           : create an index file *.Idx (-x index_name.Idx) 

-ROI         : c=%d,U=%d : quantization indices upshifted 
               for component c=%d [%d = 0,1,2]
               with a value of U=%d [0 <= %d <= 37] (i.e. -ROI:c=0,U=25) 

-d           : offset of the origin of the image (-d 150,300) 

-T           : offset of the origin of the tiles (-T 100,75) 

-I           : use the irreversible DWT 9-7 (-I) 

IMPORTANT:
-----------

The index file has the structure below:
---------------------------------------

Image_height Image_width
progression order
Tiles_size_X Tiles_size_Y
Tiles_nb_X Tiles_nb_Y
Components_nb
Layers_nb
decomposition_levels
[Precincts_size_X_res_Nr Precincts_size_Y_res_Nr]...
   [Precincts_size_X_res_0 Precincts_size_Y_res_0]
Main_header_end_position
Codestream_size
Tile_0 start_pos end_Theader end_pos TotalDisto NumPix MaxMSE
Tile_1   ''           ''        ''        ''       ''    ''
...
Tile_Nt   ''           ''        ''        ''       ''    ''
Tpacket_0 Tile layer res. comp. prec. start_pos end_pos disto
...
Tpacket_Np ''   ''    ''   ''    ''       ''       ''     ''
MaxDisto
TotalDisto

